Build-essential is a metapackage containing essential build tools for Linux distributions such as Debian and Ubuntu.
It provides the most basic tools needed to compile C and C++ programs. It usually contains references to a large number of packages needed for software development.
"build-essential" supports the following languages:
C, C++, Objective-C, Fortran, Ada, Go and more..

#The build-essential package includes:
#cat /usr/share/doc/build-essential/list

gcc → GNU compiler for C language
g++ → GNU compiler for C++ language
make → Tool to automate build processes
libc6-dev → C libraries and header files
dpkg-dev → Debian package development tools

#Isntallation:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install build-essential -y [More advanced compiler]
#sudo apt install gcc -y  [GNU Compiler Collection https://gcc.gnu.org] #optional and other versions
gcc --version
g++ --version
make --version

